            <article class="review">
                <div >
                    <header><div><h2>DEVI AND HER FOUR BABIES</h2></div></header>
                        <div class="devi">
                            <img class="rev" width="700" height="700" src="https://i0.wp.com/strayanimalfoundationindia.org/wp-content/uploads/2021/03/devi-1.jpg?w=960&ssl=1">
                        </div>
    
                        <div class="devi-content">
                        <p>Devi was found roaming the streets very pregnant and suffering from severe skin infection and injuries. No animal, let alone a mother-to-be, should be forced to live this way. Luckily, a good samaritan came across Devi and immediately sought help for this sweet girl.
                        Rescuers immediately arranged transportation to pick her up and bring her to the vet. Once Devi arrived at the vet, she received an evaluation, an overdue bath, and medications to alleviate her infections. After an ultrasound, doctors believe Devi will most likely go into labor in 3-5 days. So, this sweet girl was sent home to foster care to get some much-needed rest before she becomes a mama. </p>
                    <p>
                        After Devi goes into labor, she and her babies will need general vet care. Unfortunately, Indian Pariah (an Indian breed) puppies have a hard time getting adopted, no matter how cute they are because people think they belong on the streets. However, this is far from the case because they deserve nothing more than a warm, loving home. So, rescuers have to plan an effective adoption drive to ensure they get adopted. It is a slow process changing the Indian breed perception, but rescuers are determined to do so.
                    </p>
                        </div>
